title: The Comix of Two Cities (both versions)
description:
Issues 1-6 'The Comix of Two Cities'
Aeon, 1996, 33 pages each
Written and Illustrated by Matt Howarth
With contributions from D.M. Kister, Michele Passman, Lou Stathis, Daniel Silk, Brenda Barrows, Ferret
  
Howarth teams up with the infamous underground musicians The Residents to present the cartoon conflict of Mole vs Chub in this 6 issue sub-limestone graphic comedy. Small portions of this series appeared in the Comix of Two Cities mini-comics published by Howski Studios in 1982 and 83.


Issues 1-6 of The Comix of Two Cities (mini-comics)
Howski Studios, 1982-1983, 16 pages each
Written and Illustrated by Matt Howarth
With contributions from some of the people mentioned above

This series was previously uploaded. I asked to have it deleted to avoid confusion when a second series with the same name was uploaded.
